== Cave? ==

The [[Ganarew]] article says this:
"The cave has a parallel with [[Cadbury Castle, Somerset|Cadbury Castle]] in that it is a cave within a hillfort. It was first inhabited in the [[Old Stone Age]] and is thus older than any other Arthurian site. ref:[http://www.vortigernstudies.org.uk/artgue/guestjakejoe2.htm "Arthur's Cave near Little Doward, Ganarew", by Joe Boyles and Jake Livingston, at vortigernstudies.org.uk]"
So is there a cave here? That source says that it's open only on Christmas Eve. [[User:Martinevans123|Martinevans123]] ([[User talk:Martinevans123|talk]]) 18:24, 4 April 2012 (UTC)

:I don't have any books on Cadbury Castle but [http://www.heritagegateway.org.uk/Gateway/Results_Single.aspx?uid=1019540&resourceID=5 Heritage Gateway] and [http://www.pastscape.org.uk/hob.aspx?hob_id=199646 Pastscape] don't say anything about a cave, and a search of Jstor didn't turn anything up. Google books only has a snippet view and I can't see the context, but Alcock, Stevenson & Musson's ''Cadbury Castle, Somerset: the early medieval archaeology'' does contain at least one reference to a cave
:{{quote|The presence of an Early Medieval settlement was originally deduced from the recognition of sherds of A- and B-ware among the finds from nineteenth-century excavations in a cave below the promontory.}}
:As I can't see the text either side of that I can't be certain whether it refers to Cadbury Castle. But Barrett, Freeman & Woodward's ''Cadbury Castle, Somerset: the later prehistoric and early historic archaeology'' [http://books.google.co.uk/books?ei=9JZ8T-H_LqfI0QXnqoy_DQ&id=1IpnAAAAMAAJ&dq=Barrett+%22Cadbury+Castle%22&q=cave#search_anchor doesn't seem to mention any caves]. [[User:Nev1|Nev1]] ([[User talk:Nev1|talk]]) 19:00, 4 April 2012 (UTC)
::My word that was quick. That's very considerate of you Nev1, to go to such trouble. I was tempted to trim the reference at [[Ganarew]] since Joe and Jake seem to be pretty "immersed" in myth amd legend. But their semi-blog site is intelligent and quite well-written. The fact that this site is limestone gave me second thoughts. Your snippet may be enough to provide a lead to more. Even to Christmas Eve opening, perhaps, which itself seems quite bizarre. Many thanks for the info, which I hope may prove useful here. [[User:Martinevans123|Martinevans123]] ([[User talk:Martinevans123|talk]]) 20:05, 4 April 2012 (UTC)

